**Class:** Wizard: School of Divination
**Race:** Drow
**Background:** Astral Drifter [[footnote]]Spelljammer backgrounds are more powerful than standard backgrounds. Instead of taking the Cleric cantrips, take a 3rd language[[/footnote]]
**Alignment:** Chaotic Neutral
**Pronouns:** He/Him

------

**Strength:** 12
**Dexterity:** 14 (+2)
**Constitution:** 7
**Intelligence:** 12
**Wisdom:** 11
**Charisma:** 16 (+1)

------

**Proficiencies:** Insight, Religion, Perception, rapiers, shortswords, hand crossbows
**Abilities:** 120 feet of darkvision, Fey Ancestry[[footnote]]advantage against charm saving throws, can't be put to sleep with magic[[/footnote]], trance [[footnote]]Elves do not need sleep, only a deep, 4 hour meditation is required[[/footnote]], Sunlight Sensitivity[[footnote]] disadvantage on attack rolls and perception checks when you or whatever you are trying to perceive is in direct sunlight[[/footnote]]
**Speed:** 30ft
**Age:** 114 [[footnote]]Aywin spent 62 years in the Astral Plane and thus is 176 with Astral Years. This time had no physical effect on his body, but allowed for an extra 62 years of study in the Astral Planes.[[/footnote]]
**Language:** Elvish, Basic, Celestial, Infernal, Deep Speech[[footnote]]Celestial, Infernal, and Deep Speech are from Astral Drifter Background[[/footnote]]
**Height:** 6 ft (Medium sized)
**Equipment:** Archimedes Sphere (Spellbook), Diary, ink pen, bottle of ink, a pouch, 10 gp

------

**Cantrips:**
* Dancing Lights [[footnote]]from Drow Magic[[/footnote]]

------

**Description:** Aywin Deepwater is a Drow, driven by an obsession with divine magic. Born as a high elf, Aywin was drawn to the call of Lolth, and was changed into something more dark, and twisted: a Drow. Despite the new abilities brought about by the darkness, Aywin's desire for divine knowledge lead him to wanting more than the Queen of Spiders herself could offer. 

Risking his new deity's wrath, he sought more, leading him to the Astral plane, where he encountered Hecate, the goddess of magic and moons. Aywin spent 62 years displaced from time, studying all forms of magic and language. Emerging from the plane, Aywin found that his desire for knowledge had not yet been quenched, and he now searches for Loki, the trickster god.

